_D_e_s_c_r_i_p_t_i_o_n:

_U_s_a_g_e:

     referenceManager()

_D_e_t_a_i_l_s:

     If no reference manager is available when it is first needed by a
     call from Python to R, this function is called to create a
     `referenceManager' instance and is then registered at the C level.

_V_a_l_u_e:

     A closure that stores R objects and returns references to them.
     The closure provides a variety of different functions to operate
     on these R objects: 

 handler: 

